thread.title: Jeffrey Bell Lost Senate Elections but Influenced Conservative Thinking

author: James R. Hagerty
title: Jeffrey Bell Lost Senate Elections but Influenced Conservative Thinking
text:
Jeffrey Bell
1943-2018
As a Republican political candidate, Jeffrey Bell was an underdog who never quite had his day. His three campaigns to represent New Jersey in the U.S. Senate all failed. Yet his impressive showing in long-shot races helped make him an influential advocate for conservative ideas.
